[normal]4.16 In our view, proceedings where the litigant is seeking to hold the state to account by judicial review are important, because these cases are the means by which individual citi
[normal]zens can seek to check the exercise of executive power by appeal to the judiciary. These proceedings therefore represent a crucial way of ensuring that state power is exercised responsibly.
