[normal]..The agency struggles with the volume of i
[normal]ts casework, which has led to historical backlogs running into the hundreds of thousands; the number of illegal immigrants removed does not keep up with the number of people who are here illegally…the agency has been a troubled organisation since it was fo
[normal]rmed in 2008, and its performance is not good enough.
[normal]…it has conflicting cultures and all too often focuses on the crisis in hand at the expense of other important work; the second is its lack of transparency and
[normal] 
[normal]accountability; the third is its inadequat
[normal]e IT systems; and the fourth is the policy
[normal] 
[normal]and
[normal] 
[normal]legal framework within which it has to operate. … IT systems are often incompatible and are not reliable enough. They require manual data entry instead of automated data collection, and they often involve pape
[normal]r files instead of modem electronic case management. 
[normal]…
[normal]The agency is often caught up in a vicious cycle of complex law and poor enforcement of its own policies, which makes it harder to remove people who are here illegally. …
[normal]UKBA has been a troubled 
[normal]organisation for so many years. It has poor IT systems, and it operates within a complicated legal framework that often works against it. All those things mean that it will take many years to clear the backlogs
[normal] and fix the system ...
